title: Alphabet Shrugs Off Advertising Slump, Driven by Search Engine
description: Google’s parent company returned to sales growth, even as an advertising slowdown continued to crimp YouTube.

title: Microsoft Beats Financial Expectations Despite Worries About Economy
description: Quarterly revenue was up 7 percent and profits were up 9 percent as the company embarked on an aggressive plan to embrace artificial intelligence.

title: Japanese Moon Landing Is Uncertain After Losing Signal Spacecraft
description: The Japanese company aimed to be the first to change the paradigm for transporting things to the moon, but that will have to wait for a future mission.

title: What May Have Been Lost If the Hakuto-R Moon Lander Crashed
description: The Ispace mission had planned to carry a number of customer payloads to the moon’s surface.

title: Commerce Dept. Outlines Plans to Fund Cutting-Edge Chip Research
description: The Biden administration announced its strategy for the National Semiconductor Technology Center, a string of facilities aimed at propelling U.S. innovation.

title: Why Researchers Turned This Goldfish Into a Cyborg
description: Neuroscientists are examining how fish navigate their world using different brain circuits unlike than those relied on by mammals like us.

title: G.M.’s Profits Fell 18.5 Percent in the First Quarter
description: The decline over the first three months of 2022 was primarily the result of the short-term costs of job cuts and slower sales in China.

title: As Carlson and Lemon Exit, a Chapter Closes on Cable’s Trump War
description: The two hosts took very different approaches, but the decisions by Fox News and CNN to shed the stars marks at least a temporary shift in the excesses of Trump-era coverage.
